radiographic_examinations.findings: Identified two novel heterozygous GNAS deletions: a 6.4-Kb deletion that includes exon 2 associated with normal methylation (57%) of exon A/B DMR; and a 1,438-bp deletion encompassing the promoter region and 5’UTR of Gsα transcripts associated with reduced methylation (32%) of exon A/B DMR.
Patient 1 had normal methylation at 57% of exon A/B DMR. Patient 2 had reduced methylation at 34%.
